Procedure.description:
Procedure Purpose: FCI VNIR Calibration
Procedure Version: TEMP VERSION for COMISSIONING Responsibility: Claudia Tranquilli / Julien Rogissart Last Modified Date: 06.04.2023
Change History:
Version TEMP: (JRo - 06.04.2023) TEST version to move the loading of the PAF to save time at step P9 FDSS false to step P8.Q4.B1.A4. Remove FDSS-true -Summer- branch.
Version 2.1: (JRo - 06.04.2023) - re-update the TT timing at Step Step P9.A2.A1.A1 to Step P9.A2.A2.A7 to ensure they are executed during TRANSITION
Version 2: (JRo - 05.04.2023) - Procedure updated (TT timing at Step Step P9.A2.A1.A1 to Step P9.A2.A2.A7) after Technical meeting in preparation of Commissioning TRR4.2 with TAS-F and ESA.
Version 1: (CT - 10.01.2023) - Procedure created. Reference FOM procedure N_FCI_I130 v7. - Added argument to set number of BLIND LACs.
Procedure Objectives:
This procedure allows performing the calibration of the FCI Visible and Near-InfraRed channels.
Procedure Overview:
- Procedure detects the current season based on the yaw-flip status and performs a scan pattern update as necessary, including new mission scenario selection. - During the last operational coverage procedure updates FWP to disable automatic BB calibration. - During the retrace between last operational coverage and first VNIR coverage, procedure (1) places the COM-I in MNDn position, (2) updates FWPto set the VNIR calibration flag to ENABLED, (3) switches VCU to NODATA mode, (4) loads the VCU-I Work Plan Configuration with the phase ID “VNIR Calibration Start”, (5) switches VCU to NORMAL mode. - Waits for 6 blind LACs. - At blind LAC #7, procedure starts commanding to resume nominal scanning, if applicable. - During the last blind LAC, procedure (1) places the COM-I in Free-Beam position, (2) switches VCU to NODATA mode, (3) loads the VCU-I Work Plan Configuration with the phase ID “VNIR Calibration End”, (4) switches VCU to NORMAL mode, (5) updates the FWP to switch the VNIR calibration flag to DISABLED. - During the first nominal coverage, procedure re-enables automatic BB calibration. - Original scan pattern is resumed as necessary.
Procedure Pre-conditions: FCI in OBSERVATION mode
Procedure Constraints: None
Spacecraft Configuration: NOM/FPM
Ground Segment Configuration: None
Remarks: None
